  "title": "ImageLayer",
  "description": "A data-only image layer: a single image (texture + resolved URL) placed as a background or foreground layer. Image layers are not rendered by the tile renderer — they are exposed as data for a renderer or follow-up scene node to consume. Parallax, opacity, tint, offset, and repeat flags are carried from the source Tiled map.",
